p: The major classes of the J. excelsa EO compounds from the second experiment were monoterpenes and sesquiterpenes, both at around 50% of the total oil ( Table 6). The monoterpene hydrocarbons (about 49%) were the major portion of the total monoterpenes, with the oxygenated monoterpenes and the bicyclic oxygenated monoterpenes being very minor. The tricyclic oxygenated sesquiterpenes (25%) were the major percentage of the total sesquiterpenes; the other sesquiterpenes included oxygenated bicyclic sesquiterpenes (about 9%), bicyclic sesquiterpene hydrocarbons (about 7%), monocyclic sesquiterpene hydrocarbons (about 6%) and tricyclic sesquiterpene hydrocarbons (about 3%). The chemical classes were not very different between the Clevenger and semi-commercial extracted J. excelsa EO ( Table 6).
